<HEADLINE>
<P>
TOWN LIFTS BAN ON RUSSIAN VODKA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HUTCHINSON, Minn. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Warmed by the thaw in East-West relations, the City Council on Tuesday 
unanimously voted to repeal a local ban on Russian vodka imposed in 1983 after 
a Korean passenger jet was shot down by the Soviets. 
</P>
<P>
Mayor Paul Ackland said the city would write a letter to the Soviet Embassy to 
inform them of the action. "We want them to know that we as a community support 
the changes being made," Ackland said. 
</P>
