<P>
BULGARIAN TRAIN DERAILS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By United Press International 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
SOFIA, Bulgaria 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
An express train derailed Monday about 50 miles northeast of Sofia, killing at 
least 15 people and injuring 100, the official news agency BTA reported. The 
locomotive and three cars of the Sofia-Varna express jumped the tracks shortly 
after 8 a.m., the news agency said. 
</P>
