<P>
OFFICIAL CRITICALLY HURT IN SUICIDE TRY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Tennessee Secretary of State Gentry Crowell, a political kingpin known as "The 
Godfather" whose office has been one target of a corruption investigation, shot 
and critically wounded himself in a suicide attempt, authorities said. Crowell, 
57, put a .38-caliber handgun into his mouth and pulled the trigger in the back 
yard of his home in Lebanon, Tenn., authorities said. Surgeons removed the 
bullet from Crowell's skull in a three-hour operation at Vanderbilt University 
Medical Center in Nashville. He was listed in very critical condition. On July 
17, state Rep. Ted Ray Miller committed suicide with a shotgun at his home in 
Knoxville while he was the focus of an extortion probe. 
</P>
