<HEADLINE>
<P>
FIVE TRACKS CANCEL PROGRAMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Five thoroughbred tracks canceled their programs Tuesday because of high winds 
and other adverse weather on the East Coast. 
</P>
<P>
A power outage at Rockingham, N.H., forced cancellation at that track, and gale 
force winds in the 50 m.p.h. range pushed the Philadelphia Park program back to 
today. 
</P>
<P>
High winds also knocked out Tuesday night's racing at the Meadowlands, along 
with the daytime card at Laurel, Md., and Finger Lakes (N.Y.) Race Track 
canceled its program because of frozen conditions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
