<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROTATOR CUFF INJURIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DR. NEIL SOLOMON 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Question: Anyone who follows sports for any length of time soon becomes as 
interested in the hospital reports as in the statistics of the game. At some 
time or other, it seems that every professional ball player is going to have an 
injury, and one of the most popular ones today is the rotator cuff injury. Why 
do so many ball players in so many different sports have a problem with this? 
</P>
<P>
Answer: There is some disagreement about whether rotator cuff injuries occur 
because of some congenital problem or simply result from overuse. The injury 
occurs in all athletes who repeatedly use an overhead arm motion: baseball 
players, football quarterbacks, tennis players and swimmers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column 
</P>
</TYPE>
