VALLEY EARNINGS: NATIONAL TECHNICAL SHOWS 9% INCREASE IN PROFIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
National Technical Systems said its fiscal third-quarter profit rose 9% from a 
year earlier on a 1% increase in revenue. 
</P>
<P>
The Calabasas company, which provides engineering and testing services, said 
net income in the quarter that ended Oct. 31 rose to $282,000 from $259,000 a 
year earlier, while its revenue edged up to $7.6 million from $7.52 million. 
</P>
<P>
For the first nine months of its fiscal year, National Technical's profit edged 
up to $895,000 from $893,000, despite a decline in its revenue to $23 million 
from $23.6 million. 
</P>
