<HEADLINE>
<P>
VALLEY ROUNDUP: STUDY FINDS HIGH RATIO OF JOBS TO POPULATION 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The San Fernando Valley has more jobs available relative to its population than 
Los Angeles County as a whole, according to a study by the Valley Industry and 
Commerce Assn., a business trade group. 
</P>
<P>
The Valley has 470 jobs for every 1,000 residents, or 13% more jobs per 
population than the 417-per-1,000 ratio for the county, the group said. As 
recently as 1982, the Valley's ratio trailed Los Angeles County's by 12%, VICA 
said. 
</P>
<P>
The Valley overall has a population of 1.3 million and 38,590 business 
establishments employing 595,000 people -- with 76% of the businesses employing 
10 workers or less, the group said. Business employment jumped 36% between 1982 
and 1986, more than triple the 11% gain in the county. 
</P>
<P>
The figures are based on data from 1986 through 1989, depending on what 
information was the most recent available, VICA said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
