<HEADLINE>
<P>
IN BRIEF: STEVENS TO BE HONORED FOR THWARTING NAZIS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Andrew E. Stevens, a native of Hungary who as a runner for Raoul Wallenberg 
helped Jews escape the Nazis during World War II, will be honored as a man of 
the year by Los Angeles Men's ORT at its annual Hanukkah brunch at 10 a.m. 
Sunday at the Century Plaza. 
</P>
<P>
Stevens, a real estate developer in Los Angeles, has a 40-year association with 
ORT, having studied at the ORT School in Munich after the war. ORT operated 
schools in Israel, the United States and 26 other countries to train Jews in 
technological and vocational fields. Information: (213) 856-0255. 
</P>
</TEXT>
