<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: FOUNTAIN VALLEY; 
</P>
<P>
COUNCIL CAN'T AGREE ON VOSS SUCCESSOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ALLISON SAMUELS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
City Council members deadlocked Tuesday in efforts to replace ousted Councilman 
Fred Voss, finally deciding to leave his seat vacant. 
</P>
<P>
When voters ousted Voss on Nov. 7, they also chose to replace him by council 
appointment rather than special election. But City Atty. Alan R. Burns said 
Tuesday that he believes that the council fulfilled its duty by attempting 
twice to appoint a replacement. 
</P>
<P>
Acting Mayor Laurann Cook and Councilman James E. Neal both voted for John 
Collins because he was the runner-up in the last election. Council members 
James Petrikin and George Scott both supported John McKnight because they had 
both worked with him on city commissions. 
</P>
<P>
Burns said he did not think a four-member council will pose a problem, "because 
the council members are not sharply divided on any issues other than this one." 
ALLISON SAMUELS 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
