<TEXT>
<P>
Degradable Plastic Boycott Sought: "Don't get Glad, get mad," two national 
environmental groups declared as they called for a boycott of plastic products 
being marketed as degradable. In a joint report, "Degradable Plastics: the 
Wrong Answer to the Right Question," the Environmental Defense Fund and 
Environmental Action contend that Hefty and Glad trash bags and Nappies and 
Tender Care diapers, among other products made from the new plastics, claim 
environmental benefits that "are either nonexistent or have yet to be 
demonstrated." But the groups' chief objection is that the degradables will 
cripple fledgling attempts to recycle traditional plastic products. 
</P>
