<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Schering-Plough to Sell Maybelline: In another sign of the fierce competitive 
forces now shaping the global pharmaceutical industry, Schering-Plough Corp. 
said it would sell its Maybelline cosmetics franchise, the last of the big 
mass-market cosmetics businesses to be put on the block. Schering-Plough said 
it would sell Maybelline, possibly to the unit's management, to focus on its 
prescription and over-the-counter drug, personal-care and vision-care 
businesses. Analysts estimate Maybelline could fetch $420 million to $560 
million, or 1.5 to 2 times its annual sales. 
</P>
