<P>
Aussies in Big Orange: The Australian Ballet, the leading classical troupe of 
its country, will appear at the Orange County Performing Arts Center Aug. 7-12, 
according to an advertisement in the latest edition of the authoritative 
Stern's Performing Arts Directory. It would be the only appearance on the West 
Coast by the Melbourne-based company next year. Center officials would not 
confirm the booking, but said negotiations with the company, last seen in Los 
Angeles in 1971, are under way. DANIEL CERONE 
