A Clarification: Inquiries by the Los Angeles-based Simon Wiesenthal Center 
have apparently averted a threat that contents of the State Jewish Museum in 
Prague, Czechoslovakia, would be sold at auction in London by Christie's. The 
possibility of such a sale were first reported last month, prompting the 
Wiesenthal center to ask for clarification of the situation from both the Czech 
government and Christie's. The center was concerned because many contents of 
the museum were seized by Nazis during World War II from Czech Jews. DANIEL 
