BRIEFLY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Emerson Electric Buys Two Firms: Emerson Electric Co. announced the purchase of 
Leroy-Somer SA, a French maker of electric motors, for $460 million. The St. 
Louis-based company also announced the $135-million purchase of McGill 
Manufacturing Co., a Valparaiso, Ind., firm that makes bearings and electrical 
products. Emerson is a leading manufacturer of electric motors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
