</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Santa Fe Railway to Start Delivery Service: Santa Fe Railway has formed a 
partnership with J. B. Hunt Transport, an Arkansas trucking company, to make 
door-to-door shipments in the Los Angeles and Chicago areas. The partnership, 
to be called Quantum, is directed at shippers of high-value merchandise, such 
as china or furniture, who do not normally ship by rail. Santa Fe said it 
expects Quantum to earn a profit immediately and to bring in $90 million in 
revenue in two to three years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
