<P>
2ND SUCCESS IN TRIDENT 2 TEST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CAPE CANAVERAL, Fla. 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A Navy submarine successfully launched a Trident 2 missile today without 
interference from Greenpeace anti-nuclear protesters who had threatened to 
enter the safety zone, the Navy said. 
</P>
<P>
The launch from the submerged nuclear submarine Tennessee was the second 
straight successful undersea firing of the Navy's newest and deadliest nuclear 
weapon. Two of the first three submarine tests failed explosively. 
</P>
<P>
A 60-foot Greenpeace ketch, the Mondeivitano, was on the scene but did not 
attempt to enter a safety zone after the Navy warned it to keep away, the Navy 
said. On Dec. 4, a Navy ship damaged a Greenpeace vessel with 25 protesters 
aboard by bumping it and using fire hoses to pour water down the smokestacks, 
stopping the engines. 
</P>
