<TEXT>
<P>
Jailed black nationalist leader Nelson Mandela, whose release is expected 
within weeks, met today with President Frederik W. de Klerk about the prospects 
for black-white political negotiations. 
</P>
<P>
The meeting, announced by the Justice Ministry, was Mandela's second with a 
South African president this year. He met with President Pieter W. Botha on 
July 5, also at Tuynhuis, the presidential office in Cape Town. 
</P>
