<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE SIDELINES; 
</P>
<P>
CUBS MAKE PERRY A FREE AGENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times wire services 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
CHICAGO 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Chicago Cubs will not tender a contract to left-handed pitcher Pat Perry, 
which makes him a free agent, team officials said today. 
</P>
<P>
Perry was 0-1 with a 1.77 ERA in 19 games, said Cubs spokeswoman Sharon 
Pannozzo. He worked 35 2/3 innings. 
</P>
<P>
Perry was placed on the 15-day disabled list June 17 with tendinitis of his 
left shoulder. He spent the remainder of the season on the disabled list. 
</P>
<P>
He underwent arthroscopic surgery to his left shoulder Nov. 10. 
</P>
</TEXT>
